The paper deals with the problem of containment of schema mappings for data exchange, which is a fundamental problem in the field of databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of LAV TGDs as target constraints, which is a topic related to logic (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the decidable nature of the problem, which is a topic related to computational complexity (cs.CC).
